*) First, choose one of the pre-prepared setups depending on the precision you want:
  1) Select one of the 'parfile_input_*dx_*dt':
     - Rename it to 'parfile_input' (and replace any other 'parfile_input' used before).
  2) Select one of the 'interfaces_input_*dx_*dt':
     - Rename it to 'interfaces_input' (and replace any other 'interfaces_input' used before).

*) Then, choose your test:
  1) Fluid to solid test:
    a) Select source file 'source_input_fluid':
       - Rename it to 'source_input' (and replace any other 'source_input' used before).
    b) For now, a switch to produce plane waves in the middle of the fluid domain does not exist in the parfile. Thus:
       - Go in 'prepare_source_spatial_function.f90'.
       - Play with the 'Plane waves tests.' section.
       - Simply setting 'if(.false.)' to 'if(.true.)' should be sufficient with this EXAMPLE.

  2) Solid to fluid test:
    a) Select source file 'source_input_solid':
       - Rename it to 'source_input' (and replace any other 'source_input' used before).
    b) Make sure to set NSOURCE=15 in the 'parfile_input' you selected.

*) Once the simulation has run, launch the Matlab script to compute agreements between synthetic transmission/reflection coefficients and their corresponding theoretical values.
